5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to the Department of Archives and History; to
10 amend Sections 41-6-3 and 41-6-4, Code of Alabama 1975; to
11 further provide for the composition of the Board of Trustees
12 of the Department of Archives and History; and to further
13 provide for the filling of vacancies on the board.
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
15 Section 1. Sections 41-6-3 and 41-6-4, Code of Alabama
16 1975, are amended to read as follows:
17 "§41-6-3
18 (a) The department shall be under the control of the
19 Board of Trustees of the Department of Archives and History,
20 which shall consist of one member from each congressional
21 district and the additional members selected pursuant to
22 subsection (b)as the districts existed on January 1, 2025,
23 nine at-large members, and the Governor or his or her
24 designee.
25 (b) Two additional at-large members shall be selected
26 and an additional member shall be selected from each U.S.
27 Congressional District. The additional members shall be
28 selected by the board of trustees and their names shall be
