107 "§41-6-4
108 (a) The board of trustees shall fill all vacancies
109 occurring on the board, whether by expiration of term of
110 service or by death or resignation, but the names of all
111 successor members shall be communicated to the current session
112 or the next ensuing regular session of the state Senate for
Page 4

or the next ensuing regular session of the state Senate for
HB169 Engrossed
113 confirmation. If the Senate rejects any successor trustee, the
114 board shall proceed forthwith to fill the vacancy.All
115 appointments made by the Governor shall be subject to
116 consideration by the Senate Committee on Confirmations as the
117 committee deems necessary. An appointee shall continue to
118 serve his or her term from the date of appointment unless and
119 until the Senate Committee on Confirmations elects to consider
120 the appointment and subsequently rejects the appointment. If
121 the Senate Committee on Confirmations rejects an appointment,
122 the Secretary of the Senate shall forward the rejection to the
123 Governor and request a new individual be appointed.
124 (b) A trustee An individual appointed to succeed a
125 member whose term has expired shall serve for a term of six
126 years. A person An individual appointed to fill a vacancy
127 occurring by death or, resignation, or removal shall only
128 serve out the unexpired term of his or her predecessor. A
129 person whose appointment to the board has been confirmed by
130 the Senate shall serve beyond his or her expired term until a
131 successor has been confirmed by the Senate.
132 (c) The board shall hold at the State Capital at least
133 one regular meeting during every year and as many special
134 meetings as may be necessary, and at any meeting. a A majority
135 of the trustees board members shall constitute a quorum. The
136 Governor of the state, or his or her designee, shall be a
137 voting member of the board as authorized by Section 41-6-3,
138 and he or she shall, as far as possible, shall lend every
139 encouragement to the success and upbuilding development of the
140 department. The director shall be the secretary of the board.
Page 5

department. The director shall be the secretary of the board.
HB169 Engrossed
141 The trustees Members of the board shall receive no
142 compensation for their services. Each member of the board of
143 trustees shall be reimbursed at the same per diem and travel
144 allowance amounts paid by law to state employees for each day
145 of attendance of the business of the board.
146 (d) The board may do all of the following:
147 (1) Adopt rules for its own government and also for the
148 government of the department.
149 (2) Elect a director and provide for the selection or
150 appointment of other officials or employees as may be
151 authorized.
152 (3) Provide for the publication of historical material
153 pertaining to the state under the supervision of the director.
154 (4) Control and expend such appropriations as may be
155 made for the maintenance of the department.
156 (5) Perform such other acts as may be necessary to
157 carry out the intent and purposes of this article."
158 Section 2. This act shall become effective October 1,
159 2026.
